From 03f52ae8b77583e4df8c789639dac32ae952435f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Howard Hsu <howard-yh.hsu@mediatek.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Oct 2025 17:08:08 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 79/89] wifi: mt76: mt7996: add support twt setup link-aware
 using link_sta

Add support for multiple link handling in TWT setup by introducing
bss_idx checks and iterating over valid links, ensuring correct flow
association and setup in multi-link scenarios.

Signed-off-by: Howard Hsu <howard-yh.hsu@mediatek.com>

wifi: mt76: mt7996: add support twt teardown link-aware using link_sta

Refactor the function parameter of mt7996_twt_teardown_request to
support MLD mode. This makes BTWT teardown correct under MLO by
ensuring per-link resolution of vif/sta context and preventing mixing
flows across links.

Signed-off-by: Howard Hsu <howard-yh.hsu@mediatek.com>

wifi: mt76: introduce mt7996_for_each_btwt_flow and mt7996_btwt_has_id

Introduce two new macros for btwt flow operation,
mt7996_for_each_btwt_flow to iterate each btwt flow currently in use and
mt7996_btwt_has_id to find the matching btwt flow by the desired id.

Signed-off-by: Howard Hsu <howard-yh.hsu@mediatek.com>

wifi: mt76: mt7996: cleanup broadcast twt flows when interface down

Cleanup broadcast twt flows when the interface is down.

Signed-off-by: Howard Hsu <howard-yh.hsu@mediatek.com>

wifi: mt76: mt7996: dump bss idx for btwt scheudle

Change debugfs output to include bss_idx in twt_stats for better clarity
and debugging of TWT configurations.

Signed-off-by: Howard Hsu <howard-yh.hsu@mediatek.com>

wifi: mt76: mt7996: add handling twt information frame callback

Add twt information frame handling to support suspend and resume
individual twt operations.

Signed-off-by: Howard Hsu <howard-yh.hsu@mediatek.com>

Use le16p_replace_bits.

Signed-off-by: Howard Hsu <howard-yh.hsu@mediatek.com>

wifi: mt76: mt7996: add update individual twt agreement status

Add the ability to update the individual TWT agreement status through
the unsolicited firmware event notification.

Signed-off-by: Howard Hsu <howard-yh.hsu@mediatek.com>

wifi: mt76: mt7996: fix individual twt setup

This commit refactors the individual twt setup flow with the following
changes:
1. The existing individual TWT agreement can be updated via the TWT
request/suggest/demand from the requesting STA.
2. When receiving TWT suggestions, the next target wake time will be
determined by the value in the TWT suggest frame.
3. The twt suggest for the existing twt agreement and the nominal
minumum twt wake duration of less then 64 can be accepted by the
responding twt sta.

Signed-off-by: Howard Hsu <howard-yh.hsu@mediatek.com>

wifi: mt76: mt7996: fix iTWT setup to use correct link_id

When an AP MLD receives an iTWT setup request from a non-MLD STA,
the driver must process the request on the correct link where the
STA is connected. Previously, the code always used link 0 regardless
of which link the request was received on.

This fix adds link_id parameter to mt7996_mac_itwt_setup function
and uses it to dereference the correct station and vif link, matching
the behavior of mt7996_mac_btwt_setup.

Fixes the case where a non-MLD STA sends TWT setup on link 1 (5G)
but the AP incorrectly adds the agreement to link 0 (2.4G).

Signed-off-by: Howard Hsu <howard-yh.hsu@mediatek.com>
